`{{ plugin_name }}` is a cross-tool plugin built on the docks scaffold — skills surface in every agentskills.io runtime (Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode). This root file stays repo-wide; per-area conventions load lazily from nested `AGENTS.md` nodes (see Context tree).

## Repository scope

```
.
├── plugins/{{ plugin_name }}/
│   ├── .claude-plugin/plugin.json    Claude plugin manifest
│   ├── .codex-plugin/plugin.json     Codex plugin manifest
│   └── skills/                       cross-tool skills (productivity/, engineering/)
├── .claude-plugin/marketplace.json   Claude marketplace catalog
├── .agents/plugins/marketplace.json  Codex marketplace catalog
├── .codex/agents/                    repo-local Codex plan lifecycle wrappers
├── docs/plans/                       plan lifecycle (bootstrapped by plan-workspace)
└── scripts/                          author-side validators
```

## Context tree

Per-area conventions live in nested `AGENTS.md` nodes, each paired with a one-line `CLAUDE.md` (`@AGENTS.md`) so Claude Code's descendant walker finds them:

| Node | Covers |
|---|---|
| `docs/plans/AGENTS.md` | plan lifecycle + conventions |
| `plugins/{{ plugin_name }}/skills/AGENTS.md` | skill authoring rules |
| `scripts/AGENTS.md` | validators + CI |

The `context-tree` skill maintains these nodes; `scripts/tree/guard.mjs` enforces the pair convention.

## Codex plan agents

The plan contract has five exact owners: `plan-workspace` bootstraps, migrates, audits, or explicitly refreshes the workspace; public `plan-creator` drafts, self-reviews, and commits one previously nonexistent plan; public `plan-manager` owns every existing-plan operation, review orchestration, receipt, and lifecycle write; internal `plan-reviewer` returns sealed-bundle evidence; and internal `plan-repairer` returns one exact accepted-blocker patch or `cannot_repair`. Only `.codex/agents/plan-manager.toml` and `.codex/agents/plan-reviewer.toml` exist as repo-local wrappers; the other three skills run without wrappers. For creation, manager proves the canonical path is missing and routes to creator, creator returns the closed `PlanCreatedV1` handoff, and main context may separately invoke manager review with lifecycle intent `none`. Current schema 6 uses one `gpt-5.6-sol`/high/Standard primary reviewer, with Claude Fable/high then Opus/xhigh as availability-only fallbacks. Main-context manager alone dispatches review, reconciles findings, writes persisted orchestration and receipts, applies lifecycle, and may call repairer once for the complete accepted independently reproduced blocking set. Review has one full round plus at most one changed-input repair round; Session Relay is invalid evidence. Historical schemas 1–5 are validation-only and retain their exact persisted meanings.

## Tool-agnostic rules

- Run `corepack enable && pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` once, then `node scripts/tree/guard.mjs` and `node scripts/skills/guard.mjs plugins/{{ plugin_name }}/skills` before commit
- Skill bodies stay ≤500 lines per agentskills.io spec (sweet spot 80–310)
- Manifest versions stay in lockstep across both `plugin.json`s and both marketplace catalogs
